; Card maize-122: a B* or Q* subregister on a floating-point operand is illegal
; (FP operands are binary32 = H0/H1 or binary64 = W0). mazm must reject this at
; assemble time with a clear diagnostic rather than emitting a form the VM would
; trap. The B0 destination subregister below is the illegal case.

$0000`0000:
    CP $3FC00000 R0.H0
    FADD R0.H0 R1.B0
    HALT
